	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />The YMZ parts have the divide-by-2 already included inside. <br />If you compare the datasheet for the AY-3-8910 for the datasheet of the YMZ284, the former says &quot;the frequency of each square wave [...] is obtained by [dividing] the input clock by 16 , then [dividing] by the programmed 12-bit Tone Period value.&quot; The YMZ284 datasheet instead says &quot;F_t = F_master / 32Â·TP&quot;.<br />I think this revised plan looks ok.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


